BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION
a.  To find the [`y`]-intercept, compute [`[$f](0)=[$fof0]=[$c]\text{.}`] So the [`y`]-intercept is [`[$yint]\text{.}`]

a.  The quadratic function is given in factored form. For the output to be [`0\text{,}`] either

    [```\newcommand{\amp}{&}
    \begin{aligned}
    [$left]\amp=0\amp\amp\text{or}\amp[$right]\amp=0\\
    [$p]x\amp=[$q]\amp\amp\text{or}\amp[$r]x\amp=[$s]\\
    x\amp=[$r1]\amp\amp\text{or}\amp x\amp=[$r2]\text{.}
    \end{aligned}
    ```]

    So the [`x`]-intercepts are [`\left([$r1], 0\right)`] and [`\left([$r2], 0\right)\text{.}`]

END_PGML_SOLUTION

